ZH: 过年的时候我们放了很多爆竹。
EN: During Chinese New Year, we set off a lot of firecrackers.

ZH: 爆竹声声，喜气洋洋。
EN: The sound of firecrackers fills the air with joy.

ZH: 我们在庭院里燃放爆竹庆祝节日。
EN: We set off firecrackers in the courtyard to celebrate the holiday.

ZH: 爆竹的声音每年都让我兴奋。
EN: The sound of firecrackers excites me every year.

ZH: 孩子们在院子里尽情燃放着爆竹。
EN: The children are setting off firecrackers in the yard.

ZH: 燃放爆竹是庆祝传统节日的一部分。
EN: Setting off firecrackers is part of celebrating traditional holidays.

ZH: 每逢春节，家家户户都会燃放爆竹。
EN: Every Spring Festival, households set off firecrackers.

ZH: 爆竹声响，辞旧迎新。
EN: The sound of firecrackers rings in the New Year.

ZH: 燃放爆竹是中国传统文化的一部分。
EN: Setting off firecrackers is a part of traditional Chinese culture.

ZH: 大年初一一到，人们开始燃放爆竹。
EN: On the first day of the Chinese New Year, people start setting off firecrackers.

ZH: 爆竹声是节日的标志之一。
EN: The sound of firecrackers is one of the symbols of the festival.

ZH: 爆竹声声，洋溢着欢乐的气息。
EN: The sound of firecrackers is filled with a joyful atmosphere.

ZH: 小朋友们在街上欢快地燃放着爆竹。
EN: The children are happily setting off firecrackers in the street.

ZH: 爆竹声响彻整个村庄。
EN: The sound of firecrackers echoes throughout the entire village.

ZH: 爆竹声里，处处彰显着节日的喜庆。
EN: In the sound of firecrackers, the joy of the festival is everywhere.

ZH: 过年的时候，村里处处传来爆竹声。
EN: During Chinese New Year, the sound of firecrackers can be heard everywhere in the village.

ZH: 爆竹声传遍大街小巷。
EN: The sound of firecrackers spreads throughout the streets and alleys.

ZH: 爆竹声声，让人倍感喜庆。
EN: The sound of firecrackers makes people feel doubly joyful.

ZH: 放爆竹是一个老传统。
EN: Setting off firecrackers is an old tradition.

ZH: 新年的第一声爆竹，代表着新的开始。
EN: The first firecracker of the New Year represents a new beginning.
